name: CAPS Group
note: Can we meet today at 13:00 CET?

need_candidates.comment_requirements:
The customers are going to open new stores in Ukraine and the company CAPS Group will be providing those furniture from Poland and the person in this position would be responsible for coordination of work

CAPS Group provide fixtures, fit-out and maintenance services for interiors and display within retail, hospitality and other commercial environments across Europe and beyond.
Everyone in our international team brings a set of unique qualities. We encourage “out of the box” thinking to provide our customers with exceptional and positive experiences.
Do you believe that the sum of small things creates great changes? Join our team!

Field Operations Manager
Workplace: Lviv, Kyiv
Responsibilities:
    • Coordinates and oversees the execution of onsite customer’s projects in collaboration with multiple internal departments and subcontractors.
    • Evaluates all factors influencing the project, identifies and assesses risks and provides adequate solutions,
    • Coordinates cooperation with subcontractors and negotiates terms of cooperation,
    • Monitors progress and make adjustments as needed in the planned onsite works,
    • Evaluates project performance to identify areas for improvement,
    • Develops and maintains long-term relationships with customers and subcontractors.
Requirements:
    • Previous experience in a similar position,
    • Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and to set and meet deadlines while maintaining high standards of accuracy and quality,
    • Good understanding of furniture assembly process,
    • Good communication skills in English,
    • Knowledge of estimating, planning, tracking and controlling projects,
    • Customer focus and attention to detail,
    • Ability to work in a dynamic work environment.

We offer:
    • Work in a professional, friendly and international environment, 
    • Independency and ability to plan your own tasks,
    • Opportunity to demonstrate and implement your own ideas.

 - The proposed salary; This is the first such a position in Ukraine so we would be open for candidates feedback on their expected salary.
 - The work schedule; 8:00 am – 4:00 pm. Some days during installations these working hours can be different. We are looking for someone who will be flexible.
 - Employment terms; We offer B2B contract with 26 days of paid holidays per year.
 - The urgency for filling this position, and when you plan to inaugurate new stores in Ukraine. We are looking for an immediate hire. The maximum time we can wait for a candidate to start is a month.

Website: rh-s.com

Company website: https://www.libertyjai.co.uk/

Company info:  Liberty Jai Ltd is an e-commerce logistics consultancy established in 2018 by Jerrad Hampson, leveraging over 30 years of industry experience. They specialize in increasing sales, improving financial outcomes, and enhancing profitability for a range of clients across logistics, distribution, and e-commerce sectors. With a unique approach of working with only one client per touchpoint to avoid conflicts of interest, Liberty Jai offers services in business development, strategic advice, appointment generation, and digital support, engaging with senior decision-makers across various industries in the UK, Europe, and globally.

client_candidates.comment:
The main task for the candidate will be to conduct calls with customers: to introduce himself on behalf of the company to make a small presentation and also offer the client to contact the head of the company to discuss all the details, the number of calls presumably 100 pieces per day.
Jerrad thought that the main task for Kseniya will be not to make calls but to work with lead generation, LinkedIn, e-mail, to enter correspondence with potential clients and schedule calls with them, which will be conducted by Jerrad.

We interviewed candidate for Liberty Jai company to replace Ksenia. 

Candidates: Daria https://rh-s.com/app/managers/lead-generator/daria-d

Position: LG/Sales Asistant 

Responsibilities:
-Working with CRM systems (HubSpot)
-Making outbound telephone calls to potential clients
-Scheduling appointments for Will Slack with prospective clients
-Email communication and chatting with potential customers
-Targeting companies regarding logistics, supply chain, and other related services
-Booking meetings to discuss logistics and supply chain solutions

Result:
Daria demonstrated a basic understanding of the role and expressed willingness to perform the tasks required. She acknowledged that her current internet connection issue is temporary and not a recurring problem. Daria assured that she would try her best to find new customers and book meetings, though she mentioned that her performance might not be at the highest level initially.

Start Date: Pending decision

Next Step: Will Slack will discuss the interview with his managing director, who is currently on holiday. Follow up with a decision via email within the next few days.(31//05)
